<DOC><DOCNO> AP891128-0212 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-28-89 1651EST</FILEID><FIRST>r f AM-Avon-Chartwell     11-28 0202</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Avon-Chartwell,0211</SECOND><HEAD>Investor Group Increases Stake in Avon</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   An alliance of powerful investors includingoil fortune heir Gordon P. Getty said Tuesday it had increased itsstake in Avon Products Inc., the cosmetics company, to 8 percent.   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,Chartwell Associates, a limited partnership, said it had purchasedan additional 652,800 Avon shares, increasing its stake from 6.9percent earlier this month.   Avon, which previously vowed to fight to maintain itsindependence, has twice thwarted unsolicited takeover efforts thisyear, including one by Dallas-based Mary Kay Corp. the parent ofMary Kay Cosmetics.   A spokesman for New York-based Avon, John Cox, declined tocomment on the latest development.   Partners in Chartwell Associates include a senior executive ofMary Kay, the Gordon P. Getty Family Trust and the Fisher realestate family of New York.   In the SEC filing, Chartwell Associates said it bought 652,800shares between Nov. 15 and Monday for prices ranging from $36 to$37 per share.   Earlier this year, Avon rejected outright takeover proposalsfrom the direct sales company Amway Corp. of Ada, Mich., and fromMinneapolis-based investor Irwin Jacobs. Avon also rejectedtakeover feelers from Mary Kay.</TEXT></DOC>